J&J, Makers of Metal Hips Receive FDA Request for Data on ‘Adverse Events’

-- B y   G r e g   F a r r e l l
-- 
2011-05-10T19:23:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-10/j-j-makers-of-metal-hips-receive-fda-request-for-data-on-adverse-events-.html
The U.S. Food and Drug Administration
said it asked makers of metal-on-metal hip replacement systems
to provide data on ion concentrations and “adverse events”
associated with the devices.  Companies that received the inquiry include  Johnson &
Johnson (JNJ) ,  Stryker Corp. (SYK) ,  Zimmer Holdings Inc. (ZMH)  and Biomet Inc.,
according to the FDA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Greg Farrell in New York at 
 gregfarrell@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
